text: Hey, this is Anshu Misra ,can someone please suggest a repo,project or a bug to start with contributing, anything that would be helpful for GSoC.

elements.text: Hey, this is Anshu Misra ,can someone please suggest a repo,project or a bug to start with contributing, anything that would be helpful for GSoC.

text:
Hi Anshu!

The main period to discuss GSoC projects ideas is February 22 - March 19, so potential mentors will be adding project ideas up to this time and even into the application period (see <https://developers.google.com/open-source/gsoc/timeline> for timeline).

But you can start looking through the projects that have already been proposed here: <https://github.com/rstats-gsoc/gsoc2023/wiki/table-of-proposed-coding-projects>.

All project proposals have easy, medium and hard exercises to complete as part of the application process, so you can look through those to see if you think you could tackle them (an applicant will obviously have a better chance if they can attempt all three levels) and perhaps try a few easy exercises to see how you get on.

It is difficult to point to a particular bug that will directly help with GSoC, but helping with bug analysis/fixing will help improve your R programming skills in general and experience could help support a GSoC application. I'll post a bug in the <#C01EVRJRYA0|> channel for you/anyone else to have a go at to get started.
